# SafeHaven Pi — udev rule to trigger wlan1 recovery on device appearance.
#
# Why this file exists:
# systemd's BindsTo/PartOf correctly propagates state when the USB adapter
# DISAPPEARS (our service stops cleanly). But on device REAPPEARANCE, none
# of BindsTo / PartOf / WantedBy=device reliably pulls the service back
# in for USB hot-plug cycles — the .device unit lifecycle just doesn't
# propagate forward through those relationships the way regular unit
# starts do.
#
# This udev rule is the missing piece. It fires every time the kernel
# registers a new network interface named wlan1 (cold boot, warm reboot,
# USB plug-in, USB reseat) and explicitly tells systemd to start our
# recovery service. Combined with the service's BindsTo for graceful
# shutdown, the system fully auto-heals on cable wiggles without any
# manual intervention.
#
# Installed to /etc/udev/rules.d/90-safehaven-wlan1.rules by install.sh.

SUBSYSTEM=="net", ACTION=="add", KERNEL=="wlan1", TAG+="systemd", ENV{SYSTEMD_WANTS}="safehaven-wlan1-ip.service"
